remarks.format:
  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-102">Speech の既定のセマンティック形式は、[音声認識 (sisr) バージョン1.0 の W3C セマンティック解釈](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201765)に準拠しています。この`tag`場合、スクリプトを含む`semantics/1.0`要素の形式はです。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-102">The default semantic format for System.Speech conforms to the W3C [Semantic Interpretation for Speech Recognition (SISR) Version 1.0](https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201765), where the format for `tag` elements that contain script is `semantics/1.0`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-103">この形式を使用して<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag>オブジェクトのスクリプトを指定する必要があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-103">You must specify the script for <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> objects using this format.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-104">の構文は次`semantics/1.0`のとおりです。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-104">In the syntax of `semantics/1.0`:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-105">コンテナールール要素のルール変数は、"out" によって識別されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-105">The Rule Variable of the containing rule element is identified by "out".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-106">コンテナーのルール要素の外部にあるルール要素のルール変数にアクセスできるオブジェクトの名前は、"rules" によって識別されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-106">The name of the object that has access to the Rule Variable of rule elements outside the containing rule element is identified by "rules".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-107">(発話) に一致する最後に参照されたルールの結果は、"rules. latest ()" で表すことができます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-107">The result from the latest referenced rule that matches the utterance can be represented by "rules.latest()".</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-108"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag>オブジェクトを使用して、スクリプトを使用せずに、セマンティック値を文法の語句に関連付けることもできます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-108">You can also associate a semantic value with a phrase in a grammar without using script, using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> object.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-109">次の例では、フライトの都市を選択するための文法を作成します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-109">The following example creates a grammar for choosing the cities for a flight.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-110">この例で<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag>は、を使用して、都市の空港のコードである各都市にセマンティック値を割り当てます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-110">The example uses <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> to assign a semantic value to each city, which is the code for the city's airport.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-111">また、この例<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag>では、を使用し<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>て、という名前`cityRef`のオブジェクトによって作成された 2 `cities`つの参照のそれぞれに対して、という名前の<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>オブジェクトに個別のセマンティックキーを割り当てます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-111">The example also uses <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> to assign a separate semantic key for each of the two references made by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> object named `cityRef` to the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object named `cities`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-112">セマンティックキーは、出発地として認識されている都市、またはフライトの到着市を識別します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-112">The semantic keys identify a recognized city as the departure city or the arrival city for the flight.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-113"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized>イベントのハンドラーは、キーを使用して、認識結果からセマンティクスを取得します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-113">The handler for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized> event uses the keys to retrieve the semantics from the recognition result.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-114">コード例では、"out" は、含ん<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>でいるの規則変数を参照します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-114">In the code example, "out" refers to the Rule Variable of the containing <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-115">式 "out.Leavingfrom "は、という名前`LeavingFrom` `bookFlight`のルールでルール変数の名前が付けられたプロパティを参照します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-115">The expression "out.LeavingFrom" refers to the property named `LeavingFrom` of the Rule Variable on the rule named `bookFlight`.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-116">式 "rules. 観光都市" は、 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A>が`flightCities`で、ルール参照のターゲットであるルールのルール変数を参照します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-116">The expression "rules.flightCities" refers to the Rule Variable on the rule whose <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> is `flightCities`, and which is the target of a rule reference.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-117">この例では、"out" という式を使用します。Leavingfrom = ルール。「」と<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A>いう名前`bookFlight`の規則の規則変数`LeavingFrom`のプロパティ`flightCities`に、がある規則から値を割り当てます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-117">In the example, the expression "out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;" assigns the value from the rule whose <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> is `flightCities` to the property named `LeavingFrom` of the Rule Variable on the rule named `bookFlight`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-118">詳細については、「[セマンティック結果の内容](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/622291af-615c-4a15-9014-2933aa3f89fe)、[文法規則名参照](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/0777e975-8665-4cc3-957b-752743cb1bb9)、および[文法規則リファレンス](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/dec3a809-9aa2-4139-893f-3a549ca1e03e)」を参照してください。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-118">See [Semantic Results Content](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/622291af-615c-4a15-9014-2933aa3f89fe), [Grammar Rule Name Referencing](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/0777e975-8665-4cc3-957b-752743cb1bb9), and [Grammar Rule Reference Referencing](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/dec3a809-9aa2-4139-893f-3a549ca1e03e) for more information.</span></span>  
  
```  
using System;  
using System.Speech.Recognition;  
using System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar;  
  
namespace SampleRecognition  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    static void Main(string[] args)  
  
    // Initialize a SpeechRecognitionEngine object.  
    {  
      using (SpeechRecognitionEngine recognizer =  
         new SpeechRecognitionEngine(new System.Globalization.CultureInfo("en-US")))  
      {  
  
        // Create a rule for the cities, assign a semantic value to each city.  
        SrgsRule cities = new SrgsRule("flightCities");  
        SrgsItem chi = new SrgsItem("Chicago");  
        chi.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"ORD\";"));  
        SrgsItem bos = new SrgsItem("Boston");  
        bos.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"BOS\";"));  
        SrgsItem mia = new SrgsItem("Miami");  
        mia.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"MIA\";"));  
        SrgsItem dal = new SrgsItem("Dallas");  
        dal.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"DFW\";"));  
  
        SrgsOneOf airports = new SrgsOneOf(chi, bos, mia, dal);  
        cities.Add(airports);  
        cities.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Private;  
  
        // Create a rule reference to the rule for cities.  
        SrgsRuleRef cityRef = new SrgsRuleRef(cities);  
  
        // Create the root rule for the grammar.  
        SrgsRule bookFlight = new SrgsRule("flightBooker");  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsItem("I want to fly from"));  
        bookFlight.Add(cityRef);  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;"));  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsItem("to"));  
        bookFlight.Add(cityRef);  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out.GoingTo=rules.flightCities;"));  
        bookFlight.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
        // Initialize the SrgsDocument, set the root rule, add rules to the collection.  
        SrgsDocument itinerary = new SrgsDocument(bookFlight);  
        itinerary.Rules.Add(cities);  
  
        // Create a Grammar object and load it to the recognizer.  
        Grammar g = new Grammar(itinerary);  
        g.Name = ("City Chooser");  
        recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(g);  
  
        // Configure recognizer input.                  
        recognizer.SetInputToDefaultAudioDevice();  
  
        // Attach a handler for the SpeechRecognized event.  
        recognizer.SpeechRecognized +=  
          new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(recognizer_SpeechRecognized);  
  
        // Start recognition.  
        recognizer.RecognizeAsync();  
        Console.WriteLine("Starting asynchronous recognition...");  
  
        // Keep the console window open.  
        Console.ReadLine();  
      }  
    }  
  
    // Write to the console the text and the semantics from the recognition result.  
    static void recognizer_SpeechRecognized(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Speech recognized: " + e.Result.Text);  
      Console.WriteLine();  
      Console.WriteLine("Semantic results:");  
      Console.WriteLine("  The departure city is: " + e.Result.Semantics["LeavingFrom"].Value);  
      Console.WriteLine("  The arrival city is: " + e.Result.Semantics["GoingTo"].Value);  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="57cd2-119">上記の例のコードによって生成される文法の XML 形式を次に示します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="57cd2-119">The following is the XML form of the grammar generated by the code in the example above.</span></span>  
  
```xml  
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>  
<grammar xml:lang="en-US" root="flightBooker" tag-format="semantics/1.0"   
version="1.0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar">  
  
  <rule id="flightBooker" scope="public">  
    <item> I want to fly from </item>  
    <ruleref uri="#flightCities" />   
    <tag> out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities; </tag>  
    <item> to </item>  
    <ruleref uri="#flightCities" />   
    <tag> out.GoingTo=rules.flightCities; </tag>  
  </rule>  
  
  <rule id="flightCities" scope="private">  
    <one-of>  
      <item> Chicago <tag> out="ORD"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Boston <tag> out="BOS"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Miami <tag> out="MIA"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Dallas <tag> out="DFW"; </tag></item>  
    </one-of>  
  </rule>  
  
</grammar>  
```
